# Backend environment variables for the RECON app.
# Copy this file to `.env` (same directory) and fill in any values you need.
# The backend auto-loads .env at startup.

# ────────── Invoice-PDF extraction (General List template) ──────────
# Extraction uses the Claude Agent SDK, which talks to the local `claude` CLI.
# Authentication comes from `claude setup-token` (Max / Pro subscription) —
# NO ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is required. In fact the backend explicitly blanks
# the key out in the CLI subprocess so a stale key can't force API-key auth.
#
# One-time setup on the machine running uvicorn:
#   1. Install Claude Code  → https://docs.claude.com/claude-code
#   2. Sign in              → run `claude setup-token` (uses your subscription)
#   3. Restart the backend

# Optional — pin a specific model (e.g. "claude-opus-4-7"). Omit to use
# the subscription's default model.
# RECON_EXTRACT_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7
